	<element name="Level 11: Peerless Technique" type="Archetype Feature" source="Tregolani Homebrew Collection for Solandria" id="ID_TREGOLANI_HB_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_MONK_KENSEI_PEERLESS_TECHNIQUE">
		<description>
			<p>Through rigorous practice, you have developed deadly weapon techniques which can lay waste to any foolish enough to challenge you. You gain one of the following feature options of your choice. As an action while wielding one of your Kensei weapons, you can expend 3 Focus Points to unleash your chosen technique. Each creature of your choice within its area of effect must make a Dexterity Saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes Force damage equal to three rolls of your Martial Arts die plus your Dexterity modifier. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage. Whenever you finish a Short or Long Rest, you can replace your chosen option with a different one.</p>
			<p class="indent"><b><i>Coiled Serpent.</i></b> You become a whirling dervish, striking any within a 15-foot Emanation.</p>
			<p class="indent"><b><i>Scything Mantis.</i></b> Your weapon unleashes arcing waves of force, striking any within a 30-foot Cone.</p>
			<p class="indent"><b><i>Soaring Crane.</i></b> You launch forward with blazing speed, striking any within a 5-foot wide Line equal in length to your Speed.</p>
			<p>As part of the same Action, you can expend 1 additional Focus Point and move to any unoccupied space touching the perimeter of the technique's area. This movement doesn't provoke Opportunity Attacks.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet alt="Peerless Technique" action="Action" usage="3 Focus Points">
			<description>Each creature of your choice within your chosen technique's area of effect must make a Dexterity Saving Throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 3d{{martial arts:dice}}+{{dexterity:modifier}} Force damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage. You can then expend 1 additional Focus Point to move to any unoccupied space adjacent to the area of effect; this movement does not provoke Opportunity Attacks. Whenever you finish a Short or Long Rest, you can replace the chosen option with the other one.</description>
		</sheet>
		<rules>
			<select type="Archetype Feature" name="Peerless Technique Option" supports="Peerless Technique Option" />
		</rules>
	</element>
